#note I took another 5-6 minutes on this play. I should really be blocking the triple-triple, but even then I'm not out of the woods yet; he has a fair chance of an -ING bingo on column C given the unseen pool. I liked my play a lot because I save the U for a possible Q draw and score a lot. By flipping over 5 tiles, I also have a great chance of drawing the J or X to score with. Even if he does triple-triple, he'll be emptying the bag and allow me to go out first. the downside is that he can do exactly what he ended up doing, which is fishing to open a second triple-triple! That being the case, David spotted what I think is the top option during post-morten: UNREDY# at 1J, which I didn't know. I think the difference in win percentage is probably something like 1 in 200-300 games, but I would still play UNREDY now.
